The pizza is very good, so much that I returned during the same week and brought my girlfriend. The atmosphere is clean and comfortable. Big flavorful slices. Honestly, could have used a tad more cheese. Tasty sauce. Second time in they were slammed, which equated to a lot less oven time. In and out, so it was only warm. Still very good. I'll be back again.

Editing my initial review.  Although this place has good pizza, it is impossible to know if they are open or not.  Once on a Friday I showed up and they were closed, another Friday night I tried to call and no-one answered, and finally, their website, Facebook, google, and actual shop all show different operating times so it is too much of a hassle to guess if they will be open or not.

I  know pizza and this was great pizza. I will be back.

When you want that official N.Y. Style Pizza in Downtown Tampa, go to Wall St Pizza! The flavor is on point. The cheese, sauce and crust are just right! Next time I visit Florida I'm definitely stopping by.

Great establishment! Wonderful service and great food. I love this place. I only had the cheese pizza so far but I can't wait to taste the other options.  The pizza was huge!!!!! And sooo good. The dessert was very fantastic. Overall, I had a great time.

Some friends and I were at a conference In downtown Tampa we didn’t have a lot of time but we wanted to eat somewhere good that was also fast, we found this place and so glad that we did! Be served single slices of pizza that we’re quite large and so delicious.

This Pizza was great and the prices are very reasonable. I loved the eings!  The pizza slices are big and the sauce and crust was perfect. The staff was very accommodating. I can't wait to taste the other things on the menu.

Great Pizza and great service. Came here on my lunch break yesterday thanks to my co-worker and I was not disappointed.

Very disappointed.  Ordered 2 slices of pizza and got the wrong toppings, and very few toppings (6 small pepperonis and 5 small sausages), pizza was very greasy (grease ran off slice) and very pricey.  Definitely won't be back.

The pizza is amazing but besides that not a fan at all.. ordered wings and without telling me how many I am allowed I received 12 without knowing and a price that was ridiculous for them. Not only that the wings are not good at all, very oily and dry they did not taste like wings very rubbery. Again the pizza was good but wings not so much will not order them ever again.

Came here before going to the lightning game today. Pizza was good and atmosphere is an A+. Will definitely be coming back again.
The pizza was great. And the service was awesome!!!!!! Steve made some awesome suggestions. Def will be back again!!!!!

I work for a large company and would definitely be ordering for special events
Good NY style pizza.  Lots of pizza options ready to go.

This restaurant just opened 3/19/2019, and is not really ready to open but started taking orders for pizza. They have no menu, no price list, few people who know how to use the cash register and the fountain drink dispenser is still being connected up. They invited people in on the 19th for free pizza samples. They have lots of thin crust pizza pies in a variety of toppings ready to sell slices from (see my pictures). They will supposedly offer specials for 2 slices and a beverage but aren't offering those yet. I am all for new small businesses succeeding, but should have insisted on finding out what they charged for 2 slices before I ordered. The adage "if you have to ask, you can't afford it" certainly applied here. My 2 slices arrived, and i was shocked to be charged over $8 for them with no beverage. Ouch! While they tasted okay, they were too expensive. I hope that Wall Street Pizza (which is not on Wall Street, BTW) adjusts their prices to more closely match what others are charging for pizza slices downtown ($7 with tax for 2 slices and a large fountain drink). I won't be back until they are more affordable. But i encourage you to stop in and take a look, because I do want to support small businesses-- if i can afford to.

They had a "soft opening" yesterday, (3/19/19) where they gave away slices of cheese pizza. The crust is thin, light and airy, with a great crunch - not doughy or tough and the slices were big! They employees were welcoming and very nice. I stopped in today, and they had an array of pies!!!
